<Layout title="FAQ">
  <section class="max-w-2xl pt-12 space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-medium text-neutral-900">FAQ</h1>

    <details class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer text-neutral-800">
        What is Engineering Science?
      </summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        Engineering Science is a broad engineering programme that spans mechanical,
        electrical, and software engineering, with a foundation in physics.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer text-neutral-800">
        How is it different from other engineering majors?
      </summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        It focuses on systems-level understanding rather than early specialisation.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer text-neutral-800">
        Why do you work across hardware and software?
      </summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        Many real-world systems involve both physical components and software,
        and working across both helps with end-to-end understanding.
      </p>
    </details>
  </section>
</Layout>
